        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 1:58PM PDT by NWS San Diego CA</headline>
        <description>At 157 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mt San Jacinto State Park. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northwestern Palm Springs, Mt San Jacinto State Park, Idyllwild-Pine
Cove, Hwy 243 Between Banning And Idyllwild, Banning, southwestern
Desert Hot Springs, Cabazon, Whitewater, North Palm Springs, Valle
Vista, Hwy 74 Between Hemet And Mountain Center, Morongo Indian
Reservation, and Saboba Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
